\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 108. S. orphanidis} Boiss.,{\i  Fl. Or.}{\b  1:} 651 (1867). Caespitose; stems up to 20 cm, very slender, viscid above, 1-flowered. Uppermost pair of leaves small, very close to the base of the calyx. Calyx 20-30 mm. Petals white or pale pink above, purplish beneath. Capsule 8-10 mm, almost completely exserted from calyx; carpophore 18-22 mm.{\i  Crevices of limestone rocks. • N. Greece} ({\i Athos}). Gr.
