\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 109. S. barbeyana} Heldr. ex Boiss., {\i Fl. Or., Suppl.}, 107 (1888). Densely pulvinate, with short, branched stock densely clothed with whitish, persistent leaves. Leaves linear, glabrous, with scabrid margins. Flowering stems up to 9 cm, very slender, glabrous, 1-flowered, viscid above, with 1 or 2 pairs of linear leaves. Calyx 5-7·5 mm, turbinate, glabrous. Petal-limb obcordate, pale purple. Carpophore very short. 2n = 24. {\i Crevices of limestone cliffs above }2000{\i  m. • Mountains of S.C. Greece.} Gr.
