\pard\f0\fs28 Sect. FRUTICULOSAE (Rohrb.) Chowdhuri. Perennials with elongated, woody stock. Inflorescence a raceme-like monochasial cyme with the axis simple or forked below, without an alar flower. Calyx 10-veined, clavate and widest at mouth in fruit; teeth ovate, obtuse. Seeds reniform; faces somewhat concave, striate; back concave.
\par

