\pard\f0\fs28 A very variable species, unique in the genus for its extraordinary range of polyploid chromosome numbers. The Italian plant is large-leaved with a 4- to 7-flowered inflorescence, and has been treated by some authors as a separate species,{\b  S. graefferi }Guss., {\i Pl. Rar.} 170 (1826), as has also the small plant from N. Spain & N. Portugal,{\b  S. elegans} Link ex Brot.,{\i  Fl. Lusit.}{\b  2:} 185 (1805), with a very reduced 1- or 2-flowered inflorescence. Full details and references can be found in J. Jalas & J. Suominen, {\i Atlas Florae Europaeae}{\b  7:} 80 81 (1986).
