\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 111. S. legionensis} Lag., {\i Gen. Sp. Nov.} 14 (1816). Like {\b 110} but flowering stems 15-40 cm, arising laterally from below leaf-rosettes; inflorescence usually simple, with 3-9 flowers; calyx 13-23 mm, veins scarcely anastomosing; petals yellowish or greenish; carpophore 7-12 mm, almost glabrous at maturity. 2n = 24, 48. •{\i  Spain, N.E. Portugal.} Hs Lu.
