\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 112. S. borderei} Jordan,{\i  Ann. Soc. Linn. Lyon} nov. ser.,{\b  12:} 445 (1866). Dwarf, mat-forming perennial with thick, branching stock and erect, glabrous, 1- or 2(-5)-flowered stems up to 12 cm. Basal leaves with minute papillae on upper surface, ciliate, narrowly spathulate; cauline few, linear. Calyx 8-10 mm, pubescent, with obtuse teeth. Petal-limb pink, bifid; claw ciliate, not auriculate; coronal scales ovate. Capsule c. 6 mm, broadly ovoid, equalling or somewhat longer than the pubescent carpophore. Seeds reniform, with obtuse tubercles and shallowly grooved back. {\i Mountain rocks. • E. & C. Pyrenees.} Ga Hs.
\par

